text: Grosvenor Island is one of the Canadian arctic islands in Nunavut, Canada. It lies in the Arctic Ocean, south-east of Edmund Walker Island and north-west of Patterson Island. It is part of the Findlay Group. ==External links== * Grosvenor Island in the Atlas of Canada - Toporama; Natural Resources Canada Category:Islands of Qikiqtaaluk Region Category:Islands of the Queen Elizabeth Islands Category:Uninhabited islands of Qikiqtaaluk Region Category:Islands of the Canadian Arctic Archipelago
